Summary: The document provides the timetable for the Master of Technology in Software Engineering (SE31 FT) course for the August 2023 intake. It covers the period from January to May 2024 and includes four courses: SWE5002 Graduate Certificate in Designing and Managing Products and Platforms, Digital Product Strategy, Architecting Platform as a Business, and Managing Digital Products Service Design. The courses will be taught by lecturers Eugene, Kok Liang, Wee Khee, Daniel, Nadine, Richard, Felicitas, and Scott. This section outlines the schedule for the courses "Big Data Engineering for Analytics" and "Architecting Systems For Real Time Data Processing" which will be taught by lecturers Suriya, Venkat, and Liu Fan. The courses will take place from 5 Feb 2024 to 28 Feb 2024, with classes running from 9:00am to 5:00pm on Mondays to Fridays. These courses are part of the SWE5003 Graduate Certificate in Engineering and the MTech SE program for the academic year 2023/2024. The timetable was last updated on 22/2/2024.

The SE31 FT student timetable for the AY2023/2024 academic year includes three courses: "Designing Intelligent Edge Computing" taught by Nan Zhou and Nicholas, "Humanizing Smart Systems" taught by Kok Leong and Nan Zhou, and "Architecting IOT Solutions" taught by Nan Zhou and Nicholas. The courses are held on Mondays to Thursdays from 9:00am to 5:00pm, with the first course starting on February 5, 2024 and the last course ending on February 29, 2024. This timetable was last updated on February 22, 2024.

The document outlines the timetable for the MTech SE course for the academic year 2023/2024. The course will be taught by various lecturers, including Angela, Boon Kui, Kok Leong, Martin, and Yuen Kwan. The course will run from 8 Jan 2024 to 1 Feb 2024 and will take place on weekdays from 9:00am to 5:30pm, with some exceptions on certain days where the class will end at 5:00pm. The topics covered in the course include platform security, secure software development lifecycle for agile, and design of secure mobile architecture.

The AY2023 / 2024 Semester 2 Exam Timetable includes exams for various graduate certificate courses such as Analytics Project Management, Intelligent Reasoning Systems, Engineering Big Data, Customer Analytics, Intelligent Sensing Systems, and more. The exams will take place from May 13 to May 17, 2024, with a start time of 6:30pm and end time of 10:00pm. The timetable also includes exams for MTech SE courses. This information was last updated on February 22, 2024.
